Key Match Events: Tari Eason scored a career-high 27 points and had three blocks and four steals, contributing significantly to Houston's attempted 31-point comeback.
Post-Match Reflections: Udoka is not afraid to go deep into the rotation and showed the players to get it straight and find a way to win, or he will put anyone in.
Houston's shooting struggled, shooting 33.3% from three and 41.1% from the field, which has continued since the beginning of the season.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Alperen Sengun played for only 21 minutes and was replaced by Jock Landale, who did not help Houston.
Jeff Green played for the first time this season and Aaron Holiday was also brought in for 16 minutes.
